# Project Title: Library Management System (C++)

## 1. Number of Modules
- Module 1: Book Management (Add, Remove, Update Books)
- Module 2: Student/User Management (Add, Search Users)
- Module 3: Issue & Return System (Issue books, Return books, Track status)
- Module 4: Search Module (Search books by title or ID)

---

## 2. Requirements
- C++ compiler (GCC / Turbo C++ / MinGW)
- IDE (Visual Studio Code / Code::Blocks / Dev C++)
- Operating System: Windows / Linux
- Basic file handling support (optional if using files)

---

## 3. Methodology
- Step 1: Admin adds book details into the system
- Step 2: Users register and search available books
- Step 3: User selects a book to issue
- Step 4: System checks availability and issues book
- Step 5: User returns book after reading
- Step 6: System updates book status

---

## 4. Algorithm
1. Start  
2. Display main menu (Admin/User options)  
3. If Admin selected:  
   - Add/Update/Delete books  
4. If User selected:  
   - Search books  
   - Issue book if available  
   - Return book when done  
5. Update records in system  
6. Display updated status  
7. Stop  

